{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"6997a704-796e-4d5a-99b4-9f27f0b8aeeb","content":"Update these three files:\n\n**1. `*.csproj`** — change the target framework:\n```xml\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`** — pin the new SDK:\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`** — update base images:\n```dockerfile\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\nThen run:\n```bash\ndotnet restore\ndotnet build\n```\n\nReview the [.NET 11 breaking changes](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/core/compatibility/11.0) and update any NuGet packages (e.g. `Microsoft.AspNetCore.*`, `Microsoft.Extensions.*`) to their 11.x versions.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"5c7815d5-a01f-4a78-a20b-bb049e6a0a00","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET project from .NET 10 to .NET 11. This is a straightforward question I can answer from knowledge — no codebase to explore.","outputTokens":292,"requestId":"680C:199131:11CC598:16213B7:69FFE348"},"id":"34190f00-419f-4ab1-b077-8d7512eaa12e","timestamp":"2026-05-10T01:45:50.817Z","parentId":"2265e70d-cca4-4b4d-937a-5d42e97ff266"}
